Here's the PlantUML sequence diagram for the `awslabs_benchmark-ai` system's control flow:

```plantuml
@startuml awslabs_benchmark-ai

actor User
participant "bai-bff" as BFF
participant "Executor" as Executor
participant "Kubernetes" as K8s
participant "Watcher" as Watcher
participant "Kafka" as Kafka
participant "Fetcher" as Fetcher
participant "Metrics-Pusher" as MetricsPusher
participant "CloudWatch" as CloudWatch

User -> BFF: Submit Benchmark Job (TOML)
BFF -> Executor: Validate & Forward Job
Executor -> K8s: Create Resources (Jobs/Services)
K8s --> Executor: Resource Creation Status
Executor -> Kafka: Job Started Event

loop Monitoring
    Watcher -> K8s: Poll Job Status
    K8s --> Watcher: Current Status
    Watcher -> Kafka: Status Update Event
end

par Data Fetching
    Executor -> Fetcher: Fetch Dataset/Model
    Fetcher -> K8s: Create Fetcher Job
    K8s --> Fetcher: Fetch Completion
    Fetcher -> Kafka: Data Ready Event
end

par Metrics Collection
    MetricsPusher -> Kafka: Push Metrics
    Kafka -> CloudWatch: Export Metrics
end

BFF -> User: Job Completion Status

@enduml
```